claim.claim-text:
1. A strain sensor apparatus, comprising:
a plurality of free-standing, inter-digitated fingers arranged to form an area variation inter-digitated capacitor to provide a capacitance;
wherein said inter-digitated fingers are coupled to a surface in a configuration to allow movement with bending of the surface;
wherein a change in area between the inter-digitated fingers due to lateral movement of the inter-digitated fingers results in a change of capacitance; and
wherein said strain sensor apparatus is adapted for implantation into a biological host for detecting strain.

2. An apparatus as recited in claim 1, further comprising:
a transmitter coupled to the inter-digitated capacitor; and
an antenna coupled to the transmitter;
wherein said inter-digitated capacitor functions as a sensor;
wherein said sensor, said transmitter, and said antenna are adapted for implantation in a biological host; and
wherein said sensor is encapsulated in a housing such that the sensor is sealed from the environment within the biological host.

14. An apparatus as recited in claim 2, further comprising:
a power supply;
said power supply configured for inductive coupling to a power source;
said power supply coupled to said sensor and said transmitter;
wherein said power supply is adapted for implantation in a biological host.
